enhanced_by.reason: Both methods involve modifying the internal state of the CompositeMap by adding or updating mappings.
Both methods handle the addition of mappings to the CompositeMap, though putAll handles multiple mappings at once.
The put method returns the previous value associated with the key, similar to the get method which retrieves the current value.
Both methods may throw similar exceptions related to key type and null values, providing a basis for similar exception handling in tests.
